Description:
Old Vintage English Teddy Bear in good condition. A 1970 Merrythought collectable bear. One of Britains major children's toy heirloom gift names to collect.
12 inch Light blonde plush Mohair with fully mobile limbs. He's very handsome and quite a delightful Bear. Very tactile and cuddly.
Old Vintage English Teddy Bear, 1970s Merrythought Bear 12 " Collectable Teddy Bear, Merrythought Heirloom Soft Toy She wants this Christmas Gift for Her

A beautiful Heirloom Gift.
He does have some small pin prick marks on his pads, but nothing to detract from the pleasure of owning him. He's still a lovely Bear with a genuine English heritage.
HISTORY OF MERRYTHOUGHT BEARS.
Merrythought bears came relatively late to the early bear scene in the UK, with the company being established in 1930. 
The traditional bear from this company came in ten different sizes in gold mohair and various coloured art silks. 
Merrythought teddy bears are still hand finished to this day and have always been considered very high quality British bears.

Product name: IFOULKI" VIntage Wedding BLanket, Moroccan Blanket.
Description:
"Ifoulki" In berber language mean ( Gorgeous) Authentic Berber  wedding blanket, "Ifoulki" is GOOD Size and  a  fluffy blanket in cream and off white tones. It has a stunning, original concept : fluffy bands on one side, and all the sequin decor on the  BANDS... "Ifoulki" is in excellent condition. 
✔This vintage wedding blanket is washed, dried on sun and slightly perfumed with natural fragrance, ready to use in your home.
✔* Size : 6'8"x 3'6" feets (210cm x 110 cm)
✔* Color : Cream and off white
✔* Age : 30-35 years old
✔* Condition : Excellent. 
✔* Material : Wool, cotton, metal sequins
✔Story
Formerly part of a traditional Berber tradition, but now an eyecatcher in the bedroom of every interior and vintage lover!
The handira, or also known as a 'wedding blanket’, according to Berber tradition, was entirely handmade by the bride's relatives. Wire to wire the handira spun into a whole and the hundreds of sequins were put on one by one by hand.
All of this, so the bride's 'blanket' could be wrapped around her body on her wedding day, on her way to her husbands house. Because of the countless sequins the whole village heard the bride arrive to the village.
The handira was a symbol for fertility, happiness, and serves to protect against evil.
Today, a must-have that should not be missing in your home. A stylish vintage piece of Morocco.
Use it on your bed as a bedspread or on your couch for decoration, use it as a carpet or hang it on the wall. Either way it is a real eyecatcher in your interior!

STONE DESCRIPTION :
These stones are Simulated crystals that have been treated. Meaning that the upper layer of these crystals has been treated with man-made diamond crystals in order to  create a diamond top that is made out of pure carbon to give the stones their unique sparkle and fire.

In short: you will get stones with the same beauty and sparkle as real diamonds,but for only a fraction of the price.

Product name: Travel art kit organizer complete with supplies, can be used in easel position or flat, great gift for an artist
Description:
This is a travel sized art kit that you can take with you wherever you go. You can sketch, draw or paint with the included art supplies and heavy weight paper sketchbook. Folded up, with all supplies inside, it is about 6.5 inches by 9 inches by 2 inches. 
The kit itself is made of strong, durable KraftTex which has properties of fabric, leather and paper. I have inked and dyed it to look like antique leather. It has Tyvek sleeves for the sketchbook. You can use this laid out flat or propped up as an easel. The same Velcro straps that close it are used to prop it up as an easel. 
There is a pocket on the front that can hold small, flat items. When you use up all the pages in the sketchbook, you can take it out and refill it with another one that fits.  
I include 4 watercolor pencils in a blue, green, yellow and a red hue, a small water brush that holds a bit of water, a drawing pencil, a pencil sharpener, an eraser and an ultra fine point marker. The supplies shown in the photos are examples of the supplies included but the brands may differ.

Product name: Hand painted silk scarf - Butterfly wing- butterfly scarves- chiffon scarf
Description:
Hi!
This is 100% pure silk and hand painted one-of-a-kind piece of wearable art.
"Butterfly wing" scarf is painted on 100% pure silk. As it's name it is a whole butterfly wing with rich overflowing yellow and orange colors. It is a small scarf to wear it on the neck or like a beautiful accessory to your bag.
It is round cutted and hand sewn with pure silk hem at the edges to look like a real butterfly wing.
** After the many requests for longer version of my favourite Butterfly wing scarf- now you can choose between two sizes**
 - Small wing scarf - size approx.140 cm x 35cm, approx. 55" x 14".  
 - Long wing scarf - size approx.160 cm x 35 cm, approx. 63" x 14". 
The scarf is with hand sewn pure silk  hem. The silk is semi-transparent 100% italian natural chiffon.
**This scarf is made to order and I will paint it especially for you! 
So If you want I can change the colors upon your wish - just leave me a massage! Otherwise I will make it original colour- overflowing yellow and orange palette.On the example pictures are shown  some  other versions of my  long butterfly wing scarf  in different colors.
 I'll need approx. 10-14 days to complete it and set the colors  by professional steaming process, so the silk dye bonds with the silk fibres at the molecular level. Colors are permanently fixed and sun tolerant - they will never fade.
 Because this scarf is entirely  hand painted so slightly differences may occur - but this will make it even more unique piece of wearable art.
 It's a perfect gift: unique, personal and elegant. Just for a special lady.
"Butterfly wing" silk scarf comes to you in a beautiful gift box with care instructions and signed by me certificate of authenticity to be guaranteed that you are an owner of 100% handmade and unique piece of art.
If you want any inscriptions on the scarf - just leave me a message and I will contact you for details as color and text.
For any questions or if you want something made exclusively for you don't hesitate to contact me!
Thank you for visiting my shop!
